'''Nikola Katić''' ({{IPA|hr|nǐkola kâtitɕ|pron}};  born 10 October 1996) is a Bosnian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] and the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Katić started his professional career at HNK Stolac, before joining [[NK Neretvanac Opuzen|Neretvanac Opuzen]] in 2014. Two years later he switched to [[NK Slaven Belupo|Slaven Belupo]]. In 2018, he moved to [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]], who loaned him to [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]] in 2021. The following year, Katić signed with Zürich, who sent him on loan to [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] in 2025. Later that year, he was transferred to Schalke 04.

A former Croatian youth international, Katić also made his senior international debut for [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], before switching his allegiance to Bosnia and Herzegovina in 2024.

==Club career==

===Early career===
Katić came through the youth setup of HNK Stolac, which he joined in 2001. He made his professional debut in 2013 at the age of 16, before moving to Croatian team [[NK Neretvanac Opuzen|Neretvanac Opuzen]] in March 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/876357/bivsi-stoper-rangersa-bi-mogao-pojacati-zmajeve-ovako-je-govorio-ranije-bih-je-moja-zemlja|title=Bivši stoper Rangersa bi mogao pojačati Zmajeve, ovako je govorio ranije: BiH je moja zemlja|website=avaz.ba|date=28 December 2023|accessdate=30 December 2023|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

In December 2015, he switched to [[NK Slaven Belupo|Slaven Belupo]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://epodravina.hr/nikola-katic-i-sluzbeno-postao-novi-igrac-slavena-belupa|title=Nikola Katić i službeno postao novi igrač Slavena Belupa|website=epodravina.hr|date=10 December 2015|accessdate=10 December 2015|language=Croatian}}</ref> On 7 May 2017, he scored his first professional goal in a triumph over [[NK Istra 1961|Istra 1961]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://index.hr/sport/clanak/slaven-belupo-u-pozitivnoj-seriji-u-koprivnici-pala-i-istra/968342.aspx|title=Slaven Belupo u pozitivnoj seriji: U Koprivnici pala i Istra|website=index.hr|date=7 May 2017|accessdate=10 May 2017|language=Croatian}}</ref>

===Rangers===
In June 2018, Katić was transferred to Scottish side [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://skysports.com/football/news/11788/11402695/rangers-sign-croatian-defender-nikola-katic-from-slaven-belupo-on-four-year-deal|title=Rangers sign Croatian defender Nikola Katic from Slaven Belupo on four-year deal|website=skysports.com|date=13 June 2018|accessdate=15 June 2018}}</ref> He made his official debut for the club in a [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League#First qualifying round|UEFA Europa League qualifier]] against [[KF Shkupi|Shkupi]] on 12 July.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://skysports.com/football/news/11788/11435309/rangers-2-0-shkupi-steven-gerrard-era-starts-with-europa-league-first-qualifying-round-win|title=Rangers 2-0 Shkupi: Steven Gerrard era starts with Europa League first qualifying round win|website=skysports.com|date=12 July 2018|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> On 2 August, he scored his first goal for Rangers in a [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League#Second qualifying round|UEFA Europa League qualifier]] against [[NK Osijek|Osijek]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://skysports.com/football/news/11959/11458593/rangers-1-1-nk-osijek-2-1-agg-nikola-katic-seals-europa-league-progress|title=Rangers 1-1 NK Osijek (2-1 agg): Nikola Katic seals Europa League progress|website=skysports.com|date=12 July 2018|accessdate=15 July 2018}}</ref> A week later, he made his league debut against [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://skysports.com/football/news/11781/11462114/aberdeen-1-1-rangers-steven-gerrard-denied-first-rangers-league-win-by-90th-minute-bruce-anderson-equaliser|title=Aberdeen 1-1 Rangers: Steven Gerrard denied first Rangers league win by 90th-minute Bruce Anderson equaliser|website=skysports.com|date=5 August 2018|accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref> On 20 April 2019, he scored his first league goal for the team in a defeat of [[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Hearts]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://skysports.com/football/news/11781/11698914/hearts-1-3-rangers-steven-gerrard-s-team-put-celtic-title-party-on-hold|title=Hearts 1-3 Rangers: Steven Gerrard's team put Celtic title party on hold|website=skysports.com|date=20 April 2019|accessdate=20 April 2019}}</ref>

In October 2019, Katić signed a new four-year deal with the squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://skysports.com/football/news/11788/11838001/nikola-katic-signs-one-year-rangers-contract-extension-until-2023|title=Nikola Katic signs one-year Rangers contract extension until 2023|website=skysports.com|date=17 October 2019|accessdate=20 October 2019}}</ref>

In July 2020, he suffered a severe knee injury, which was diagnosed as an [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|anterior cruciate ligament tear]] and was ruled out for at least six months. Over a year after the injury, on 24 July 2021, he returned to the pitch.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://hitc.com/great-to-see-rangers-stars-ibrox-appearance-has-these-gers-fans-buzzing|title=Great to see – Rangers star's Ibrox appearance has these Gers fans buzzing|website=hitc.com|date=25 July 2021|accessdate=25 July 2021}}</ref>

He won his first trophy with the club on 7 March 2021, when they were crowned league champions.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://skysports.com/football/news/11781/12237845/rangers-confirmed-as-scottish-premiership-champions-after-celtic-draw-with-dundee-united|title=Rangers confirmed as Scottish Premiership champions after Celtic draw with Dundee United|website=syksports.com|date=7 March 2021|accessdate=10 March 2021}}</ref>

====Loan to Hajduk Split====
In August 2021, he was sent on a season-long loan to [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/58398741|title=Rangers duo Cedric Itten and Nikola Katic loaned out for season|website=bbc.co.uk|date=31 August 2021|access-date=1 September 2021}}</ref>

===Zürich===
In August 2022, Katić moved to Swiss outfit [[FC Zürich|Zürich]] on a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport.ch/superleague/1005219/der-fc-zuerich-verpflichtet-einen-kroatischen-nationalspieler|title=Der FC Zürich verpflichtet einen kroatischen Nationalspieler|website=sport.ch|date=31 August 2022|accessdate=1 September 2022|language=German}}</ref> He made his competitive debut for the side in a [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League#Group A|UEFA Europa League]] game against [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] on 6 October.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport.ch/uefa/1022279/schwacher-fcz-kassiert-naechste-klatsche-der-meister-rutscht-immer-tiefer-in-die-krise|title=Schwacher FCZ kassiert nächste Klatsche – der Meister rutscht immer tiefer in die Krise|website=sport.ch|date=6 October 2022|accessdate=7 October 2022|language=German}}</ref> A week later, he made his league debut against [[FC Winterthur|Winterthur]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport.ch/superleague/1022569/planloser-fcz-bleibt-auch-bei-nullnummer-gegen-aengstliches-winterthur-sieglos|title=Planloser FCZ bleibt auch bei Nullnummer gegen ängstliches Winterthur sieglos|website=sport.ch|date=9 October 2022|accessdate=10 October 2022|language=German}}</ref> On 13 November 2022, he scored his first goal for Zürich in a victory over [[Servette FC|Servette]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport.ch/superleague/1040050/der-fcz-ballert-sich-den-frust-von-der-seele-ueberzeugender-fc-zuerich-bezwingt-den-servette-fc-mit-4-1|title=Der FCZ ballert sich den Frust von der Seele – Überzeugender FC Zürich bezwingt den Servette FC mit 4:1|website=sport.ch|date=13 November 2022|accessdate=15 November 2022|language=German}}</ref>

In October 2023, Katić extended his deal with the team until June 2026.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sport.ch/superleague/1183523/der-neue-fcz-sportchef-malenovic-ueberzeugt-einen-wechselkandidat-von-einer-vertragsverlaengerung|title=Der neue FCZ-Sportchef Malenovic überzeugt einen Wechselkandidat von einer Vertragsverlängerung|website=sport.ch|date=19 October 2023|accessdate=20 October 2023|language=German}}</ref>

====Loan to Plymouth Argyle====
In January 2025, he was loaned to English club [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/953718/nikola-katic-ima-novi-klub-bh-trener-ga-doveo-na-posudbu|title=Nikola Katić ima novi klub, bh. trener ga doveo na posudbu|website=avaz.ba|date=31 January 2025|accessdate=1 February 2025|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

On 9 February 2025, Katić played in [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] 1–0 win against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] in the [[FA Cup]] fourth round.<ref name="plymouth-liverpool">{{cite news |last1=Burt |first1=Jason |title=Plymouth's famous victory over Liverpool is brilliant endorsement for the Cup |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2025/02/09/plymouth-argyle-vs-liverpool-live-score-updates-fa-cup/ |access-date=10 February 2025 |work=The Telegraph |date=9 February 2025}}</ref> At the time, Plymouth was bottom of the [[EFL Championship|Championship]] while Liverpool led the [[Premier League]].<ref name="plymouth-liverpool"/> Katić lost a tooth during the match.<ref name="plymouth-liverpool"/>

===Schalke 04===
In July 2025, Katić joined German side [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] on a contract until June 2028.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/schalke-predstavio-veliko-pojacanje-nikola-katic-zvanicno-igrac-njemackog-velikana|title=Schalke predstavio veliko pojačanje: Nikola Katić zvanično igrač njemačkog velikana|website=n1info.ba|date=1 July 2025|accessdate=1 July 2025|language=Bosnian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://schalke04.de/en/team/nikola-katic-transfer/|title=Schalke complete Nikola Katic signing|website=FC Schalke 04|date=1 July 2025}}</ref>

He debuted officially for the squad on 1 August against [[Hertha BSC]], managed to score a goal and get sent off.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/schalke-savladao-herthu-debi-iz-snova-za-muslica-i-katica-1064633|title=Schalke savladao Herthu, debi iz snova za Muslića i Katića|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=1 August 2025|accessdate=1 August 2025|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

==International career==
After representing [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] at the [[Croatia national under-21 football team|under-21 level]], Katić made his senior international debut in a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] game against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]] on 28 May 2017. However, in April 2024, he decided that he would play for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] in the future.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/katic-o-dolasku-u-reprezentaciju-bih-spahic-me-prvi-kontaktirao-i-dosao-mi-kuci/240529108|title=Katić o dolasku u reprezentaciju BiH: Spahić me prvi kontaktirao i došao mi kući|website=klix.ba|date=29 May 2024|accessdate=1 June 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

In May, his request to change sports citizenship from Croatian to Bosnian was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/reprezentacija/spahic-govorio-o-gigovicu-djuricu-jasicu-ali-i-drugima-posao-nece-biti-lagan-954702|title=Spahić govorio o Gigoviću, Đuriću, Jašiću, ali i drugima: Posao neće biti lagan|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=16 May 2024|accessdate=17 May 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref> Later that month, he received his first senior call-up, for friendly games against [[England national football team|England]] and [[Italy national football team|Italy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/426658-sergej-barbarez-objavio-spisak-za-englesku-i-italiju-pozvan-i-dzeko|title=Sergej Barbarez objavio spisak za Englesku i Italiju, pozvan i Džeko|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=16 May 2024|accessdate=18 May 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref> He debuted against the former on 3 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/engleska-slavila-protiv-bih-zmajevi-u-barbarezovom-debiju-za-pola-sata-potopljeni-u-newcastleu/189628|title=Engleska slavila protiv BiH: Zmajevi u Barbarezovom debiju za pola sata potopljeni u Newcastleu|website=faktor.ba|date=3 June 2024|accessdate=4 June 2024|language=Bosnian}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Katić's cousin is [[Croats of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Bosnian Croat]] politician [[Darijana Filipović]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/vijesti/bih/darijana-filipovic-poklonila-sabini-cudic-dres-njenog-rodaka-i-reprezentativca-nikole-katica-s-brojem-18/251011049|title=Darijana Filipović poklonila Sabini Ćudić dres njenog rođaka i reprezentativca Nikole Katića s brojem 18|date=11 October 2025|access-date=11 October 2025|language=bs|author=I. Sa.|publisher=Klix.ba}}</ref>

